    {
      "id": "PopularPost64404",
      "post_content": "Ante Existed to stop people from BUYING their power. Back in 1993, what was to stop you from walking into somewhere, buying a BOX of Starter Decks, and then being unbeatable? Remember back then there was NO sissy restricted List and no banned list. If you wanted to make a deck of 20 Black Lotuses and 20 Fireballs that was perfectly Legal.\n  \n   \nSo Richard Garfield came up with the Ante, and the argument FROM Garfield was ; \"If your deck was the distilled fruit of 10 decks, then, when I do win, I win a more valuable card\" and basically he wanted a way for people who were trading and PLAYING their way to good decks, to be able to compete with the people who bought 20 Black Lotuses and whatever else and were almost un-beatable.\n  \n   \nSo when you won a game for Ante, you got a great card, which, you could trade back for cards you wanted or needed to make YOUR deck better.\n  \n   \nI really sometimes wonder why WOTC doesn't just print a Magic: The Gathering History because this is the third posting on ... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "SlackWareWolf",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost64404\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_post\">Ante Existed to stop people from BUYING their power. Back in 1993, what was to stop you from walking into somewhere, buying a BOX of Starter Decks, and then being unbeatable? Remember back then there was NO sissy restricted List and no banned list. If you wanted to make a deck of 20 Black Lotuses and 20 Fireballs that was perfectly Legal.\r<br/> <br/>So Richard Garfield came up with the Ante, and the argument FROM Garfield was ; \"If your deck was the distilled fruit of 10 decks, then, when I do win, I win a more valuable card\" and basically he wanted a way for people who were trading and PLAYING their way to good decks, to be able to compete with the people who bought 20 Black Lotuses and whatever else and were almost un-beatable.\r<br/> <br/>So when you won a game for Ante, you got a great card, which, you could trade back for cards you wanted or needed to make YOUR deck better.\r<br/> <br/>I really sometimes wonder why WOTC doesn't just print a Magic: The Gathering History because this is the third posting on ... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 64404)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '64404'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Pos